## Agent final message

> Query86 is complete and validated. The query file `query86.preql` has been written to the working directory. `trilogy run query86.preql` executes cleanly and returns 100 rows.
> 
> The query:
> - Imports `raw.web_sales` for web sales data with date and item dimensions (auto-joining via Trilogy's semantic model)
> - Filters to year 2000 using `where year(web_sales.date.date) = 2000`
> - Uses `by rollup` on `web_sales.item.category, web_sales.item.class` to compute total net paid at three grains: (category, class) detail, (category) subtotal, and grand total
> - Detects rollup hierarchy levels via hidden `grouping()` columns mapped to levels 0 (detail), 1 (category subtotal), and 2 (grand total)
> - Ranks within the appropriate parent using windowed `rank()`: category subtotals ranked together within level 1, class detail rows ranked within their category
> - Orders by hierarchy_level desc (grand total first), then category nulls first, then within-parent rank nulls first
> - Limits to 100 rows

